column5: as they say. "anyone but Stewart"

Junior's team got him in that.. taking their sweet time on the  pit stop!  Kid deserved that... pushed the 6 car for laps and laps before he was dumb and dropped down on that restart.  Notice.. not a scratch on the kids car either...
Awesome.  That was wicked.

FORD   #1  #2   #3... exactly how it should be.
Cool finish!

You seen that little "what ever kick" to the back bumper too eh?
"OMG am I dreaming!!??"  Way to go kid. Good young lad right there.
awesome race today....Lots of action for daytona..One of the best I have seen in years there..

Good for the kid, but it's gonna take some time or me to get into this new draft setup, just feela like a fix the whole way around. Doesn't feel like they are racing. No doubt they are but it just doesnt feel like racing.
thats not racing it's crap

As a huge Ford fan, it was great to see the Fords 1, 2, 3.  There have been some pretty lean years for Ford fans in Nascar and I hope this is the start of a competative manufacturer's race again.  I remember when I first got into Nascar racing in the late '80s and the Fords were competative with the Chevs( and Pontiacs, at that time ).  Still can't believe a 20 year old won the Daytona 500.  And I think his birthday was just the day before!

Also I didn't feel like I had any idea what was happening in the pits, it was just a mess the tv coverage felt so ambiguous. I am glad I am not the only one that doesn't like this dancing partner bananas versus racing. I think this will take alot of the driver versus driver out of the series. That's what I like about NASCAR. F1 I also like but it's more machine versus machine. Not as much about the driver.
